      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process means the government must respect certain fundamental personal rights, even if those rights aren't explicitly listed in the Constitution. It essentially prevents the government from taking away essential liberties without a very strong justification. This concept has been vital in civil rights cases, as courts have used it to protect rights like privacy and free expression against government overreach.",
      "source": "target",
